WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.120 --> 00:00:13.280
♫ (music playing) ♫

00:00:13.280 --> 00:00:18.630
(woman) However long your visit to our island
lasts, explore 10,000 years with us and

00:00:18.630 --> 00:00:22.700
discover the Story of Man.

00:00:29.080 --> 00:00:34.680
A story that begins here at Thie Tashtee
Vannin, the Manx Museum. Explore the art

00:00:36.740 --> 00:00:39.320
Explore the art and culture of the Manx people.

00:00:39.320 --> 00:00:42.840
Their customs and traditions 
will take you to another time.

00:00:48.060 --> 00:00:51.620
The story of man includes
11 more magnificent Heritage Sites

00:00:51.629 --> 00:00:57.360
together giving you one award-winning
experience to discover and enjoy as you

00:00:57.360 --> 00:01:03.589
travel around the island through 227
square miles of historic Manx landscape.

00:01:03.589 --> 00:01:10.520
From Douglas take the short drive to
Peel to meet our mythological sea god Manannan.

00:01:10.520 --> 00:01:14.280
(man) I know who you are. 
You are travellers.

00:01:14.280 --> 00:01:16.860
(woman) Uncover the stories 
carved in the ancient stones.

00:01:16.860 --> 00:01:20.840
Hear tales of our
Celtic and Viking ancestors and of Man's

00:01:20.850 --> 00:01:27.600
proud bond with the sea. 
(shouts and cannon blasts) 
Manannan will again be your guide at Peel castle,

00:01:27.600 --> 00:01:34.560
revealing its secrets in the history of
daily life in this ancient and dramatic island fort.

00:01:34.560 --> 00:01:37.940
To enjoy four more unforgettable
chapters in the Story of Man,

00:01:37.950 --> 00:01:42.600
be sure to spend a day with us at
Castletown, our ancient Island capital.

00:01:42.600 --> 00:01:47.480
All from Douglas travel south on the
Island's historic steam railway.

00:01:47.480 --> 00:01:50.840
(train on tracks with whistle-blowing)

00:01:50.840 --> 00:01:54.940
♫ (music playing) ♫

00:01:54.940 --> 00:02:01.320
In Castle Rushen, you can live like a king.

00:02:01.360 --> 00:02:03.360
Within its walls you can experience

00:02:03.360 --> 00:02:08.900
for yourself the good times in the
Island's history and the bad. A short

00:02:08.900 --> 00:02:15.020
(sounds of battle with horses and swords)

00:02:15.220 --> 00:02:17.220
(school bell ringing)

00:02:17.220 --> 00:02:20.490
A short walk from the castle, you can share the
school days of an older generation

00:02:20.490 --> 00:02:29.180
inside the oldest roofed building on the Island.

00:02:29.180 --> 00:02:34.410
Only two minutes walk away, another
celebration of the Manx identity awaits

00:02:34.410 --> 00:02:38.880
your discovery. This time tracing the
lives and the courage of the Manx

00:02:38.880 --> 00:02:48.030
fishermen down the centuries. And while
you're in Castletown be ready to take

00:02:48.030 --> 00:02:54.420
your seat in the Old House of Keys. Take
part in the great political debates then

00:02:54.420 --> 00:02:57.810
cast your vote with your fellow
honorable members on the laws that

00:02:57.810 --> 00:03:05.340
govern every islander's life. Should women 
get the vote? You can decide.

00:03:05.340 --> 00:03:09.959
On Man, so much of our history reaches out into the
present. Only a few minutes from Castletown,

00:03:09.959 --> 00:03:14.100
you can join our team of
archaeologists at Russian Abbey as they

00:03:14.100 --> 00:03:19.290
bring to life the early roots of Manx
Christianity. Further south, the Island

00:03:19.290 --> 00:03:24.170
has much more to reveal. You can travel
from Douglas to Port Erin by steam train.

00:03:24.170 --> 00:03:29.910
At Cregneash, you can step into the last
stronghold of Manx crofting tradition.

00:03:29.910 --> 00:03:36.840
A living, working, farming community where
the old country ways are still the only ways.

00:03:36.840 --> 00:03:40.700
At the sound you can discover a
coastline that hides a treacherous

00:03:40.709 --> 00:03:46.960
nature behind its historic past and
scenic beauty. Look across to the Calf of Man

00:03:46.960 --> 00:03:51.700
and discover its unique story
including its key modern-day role in the

00:03:51.700 --> 00:03:57.130
study of bird migration. If you travel
north, the Story of Man will continue to

00:03:57.130 --> 00:04:03.820
enthrall you. From Douglas take the Manx
Electric Railway to Ramsey where you can

00:04:03.820 --> 00:04:09.100
see and hear about the life of the
wealthy Victorian Gibb family. Their home

00:04:09.100 --> 00:04:15.620
and possessions frozen in time at the
Grove.

00:04:15.820 --> 00:04:18.380
Then at Laxey, marvel as you stand

00:04:18.380 --> 00:04:23.680
beneath the mightiest wheel of its kind
in the world. Follow in the footsteps of

00:04:23.680 --> 00:04:28.270
generations of Manx miners along the
mines trail with its echoes of a

00:04:28.270 --> 00:04:33.490
once-thriving lead industry. And if you
have a head for heights, don't miss the

00:04:33.490 --> 00:04:39.130
breathtaking view from the top of the
wheel. The Story of Man – twelve

00:04:39.130 --> 00:04:46.290
magnificent Manx heritage sites. 227
square miles of historic countryside.

00:04:46.290 --> 00:04:51.580
10,000 unforgettable years of Manx
history and culture just waiting to be

00:04:51.580 --> 00:04:57.070
explored. And with a multi-site pass, you
can discover more at the Story of Man

00:04:57.070 --> 00:05:00.000
for less.

